=directory="{{ $('Set Variables').item.json.directory }}"
subdirectory="$directory/{{ $json.folder }}";
file_list="{{ $json.files.join(' ') }}";

# create subdirectory if not exists
mkdir -p $subdirectory;

# for each suggestion, move the file into the subdirectory.
# If the file in the subdirectory exists, then we'll rename the current file by adding a small random string to the end of the filename.
for filename in $file_list; do
    if [ -e "$subdirectory/$filename" ]; then
        mv "$directory/$filename-$RANDOM" -t $subdirectory;
    else
        mv "$directory/$filename" -t $subdirectory;
    fi
done

parameters.content:
## Step 2. Identify files that need to be organised
[Read more about Execute Command node]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

For all Files in the root level of our selected target folder, we want  them to be sorted and moved into categorised subdirectories. In this step, we'll use linux commands to get a list of files and folders currently present in the target folder.

## Step 3. Using Mistral AI to organise our target folder
[Read more about Mistral AI]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

Using Mistral AI as our AI file manager, it can help us suggest which files go into which categorised subdirectory. If the subdirectory doesn't exist, Mistral can also suggest one to be created.

## Step 4. Move the files into subdirectories
[Read more about Execute Command node]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

For this step, we'll use the execute command node to execute a shellscript to move the files into their respective subdirectories.

parameters.text:
=Here is the list of current files in the directory:
{{ $json.files.map(file => `* ${file}`).join('\n') }}

Here is the list of current folders in the directory:
{{ $json.folders.length ? $json.folders.map(item => `* ${item}`).join('\n') : 'There are currently no directories' }}

Group the current files using the filename as a hint and decide which of the current folders should they be moved to. If there are no current folders, then suggest a folder to be created.

If you can't decide which folder to put the file in, the file should be moved to the misc folder.
